---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What's the typical Cardinia Lakes paving project?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Cardinia Lakes is young-family country - mortgage-belt couples in new 4-bed builds on 350-500m² lots, kids under 10, both parents working. The default 2026 paving package is: exposed-aggregate driveway (60m², $9,500-$13,500), bluestone or sandstone back alfresco patio (20-25m², $6,500-$10,500), occasionally a small segmental-block retaining wall to step the back-yard slope (under 1m, $2,500-$4,500). Total package: $18,500-$28,500 depending on stone choice and any retaining. Owners want low-maintenance materials and don't want to be hosing pavers every weekend." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why do new Cardinia Lakes driveways need such heavy reinforcement?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Cardinia Lakes was built on what used to be wetland-edge clay (the lakes themselves are an engineered feature of the development). The underlying soil is Class M to occasionally Class H reactive clay. Standard developer-spec driveways with no mesh and minimal base routinely crack within 2-3 years. Our spec for Cardinia Lakes lots: 100mm slab with SL82 mesh on 100mm compacted Class 3 base with 75µm moisture barrier and saw-cut control joints at 4m intervals. For Class H lots (engineer-confirmed) we step up to 125mm slab with SL92 mesh. Cost difference vs minimum spec: ~$15-$25/m² more. Crack-prevention value over 15 years: priceless." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can a Cardinia Lakes pool surround integrate with the alfresco patio?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes - and it's the cleanest visual outcome when the same paver continues from alfresco zone to pool surround. Two design constraints: (1) the immediate pool-edge band needs P4/R11 slip-rated finish (honed bluestone or sand-blasted sandstone both work), so we'll often use a slightly different finish of the same stone right at the pool edge; (2) the alfresco patio and pool surround want falls in opposite directions - patio falls away from house, pool surround falls away from pool - so the high point sits between them. We design the level transitions in advance, often with a grated linear drain at the high-point line." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you do small-block landscaping where the patio is competing with the lawn?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes - small-block design is exactly the Cardinia Lakes problem. A 400m² lot with the house taking 220m², garage 36m², side setbacks 80m², front lawn 30m² leaves about 35m² for the back yard. A 25m² patio + retaining + drainage eats most of that. We design with the trampoline/swing-set/dog-run in mind - the patio shouldn't consume the kids' play space. Often the right call is a smaller patio (15-18m²) plus a stepping-stone path through the lawn rather than fully paving everything. We're happy to recommend less paving if the brief calls for it." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What about the Cardinia Lakes path-network - connecting paths from driveway to back patio?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Most Cardinia Lakes lots want a side path connecting front driveway to back patio (so you can wheel bins, mowers, kids' bikes without going through the house). Typical spec: 900-1200mm wide segmental block or matched-paver path, polymeric-sanded joints, 100mm compacted Class 3 base. Cost: $130-$180/m². 12m of side path: $1,400-$2,200. If your existing path is concrete and cracked, lift-and-replace with segmental is usually similar cost to repair-and-seal and looks 100% better." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does the full Cardinia Lakes paving package take?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Driveway alone: 5-7 days (excavation, base, formwork, pour, cure, control-joint cut). Back patio alone: 5-7 days. Combined driveway + patio + side path package: typically 12-16 working days spread over 3-4 weeks (we don't run both crews simultaneously on a small lot - too cramped). Cardinia Shire crossover inspection adds 3-5 days of waiting depending on Council schedule. We schedule pours for early-week so curing covers the working week, and we communicate daily on progress." }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Layout
  title="Paving & Stonemasonry Cardinia Lakes | Driveways, Patios, Retaining | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Paving and stonemasonry for Cardinia Lakes - exposed-aggregate driveways, bluestone alfresco patios, engineered retaining walls. Class M reactive-clay base spec. Family-friendly small-block design."
  canonical="https://officerpavingco.com.au/cardinia-lakes/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Cardinia Lakes &middot; Lakeside &middot; Arena-adjacent</span>
      <h1>Paving &amp; stonemasonry in <span class="accent">Cardinia Lakes</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Cardinia Lakes is young-family country - mortgage-belt couples in new
        4-bed builds with kids under 10, second incomes, busy lives. The default
        2026 package is an exposed-aggregate driveway, a low-maintenance bluestone
        or sandstone alfresco patio, and occasionally a small block retaining
        wall to step the slope. Materials chosen so you&rsquo;re not hosing pavers
        every weekend.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free site visit</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Cardinia Lakes</span>
      <h2>The Cardinia Lakes paving story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Reactive-clay engineering is everything here.</h3>
        <p>
          Cardinia Lakes was built on former wetland-edge clay (the lakes
          themselves are an engineered feature of the development). The
          underlying soil is <strong>Class M to occasionally Class H reactive
          clay</strong>. Standard developer-spec driveways with minimal base
          and no mesh routinely crack within 2-3 years. Our default spec:
          100mm slab, SL82 mesh, 100mm compacted Class 3 base, 75&micro;m
          moisture barrier, saw-cut joints at 4m. For Class H lots we step up
          to 125mm + SL92. Cost premium over minimum spec: ~$15-$25/m&sup2;.
          Crack-prevention value over 15 years: enormous.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Small-block design that respects the kids&rsquo; play space.</h3>
        <p>
          A 400m&sup2; Cardinia Lakes lot with house (220m&sup2;), garage
          (36m&sup2;), side setbacks (80m&sup2;) and front lawn (30m&sup2;)
          leaves only ~35m&sup2; for back yard. A 25m&sup2; patio eats most
          of that. We design with the trampoline / swing-set / dog-run in
          mind - the patio shouldn&rsquo;t consume the kids&rsquo; play
          space. Often the right call is a smaller patio (15-18m&sup2;)
          plus a stepping-stone path through the lawn rather than fully
          paving everything. Happy to recommend less paving when the brief
          calls for it.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Low-maintenance is the brief.</h3>
        <p>
          Cardinia Lakes families don&rsquo;t want to be hosing pavers every
          weekend. That means: <strong>bluestone or porcelain</strong> over
          sandstone (less staining), polymeric-sanded joints (no weed
          germination, no ant infestation), and gentle falls so debris washes
          to the lawn edge rather than collecting at corners. Bluestone holds
          its colour for life and shrugs off chlorine splash if you&rsquo;re
          combining with a pool.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Side-path networks - the bit owners forget.</h3>
        <p>
          Most Cardinia Lakes lots want a side path connecting front driveway
          to back patio so you can wheel bins, mowers and kids&rsquo; bikes
          without going through the house. Typical: 900-1200mm wide
          segmental block or matched-paver path, polymeric-sanded, on
          compacted Class 3 base. Cost: $130-$180/m&sup2;. 12m side
          path: $1,400-$2,200.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Cardinia Lakes jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>60m&sup2; exposed-agg driveway + crossover permit: $9,500-$13,500</li>
          <li>20-25m&sup2; bluestone alfresco patio + grated linear drain: $6,500-$10,500</li>
          <li>Side path 12m connecting driveway to back patio: $1,400-$2,200</li>
          <li>Small segmental-block retaining wall (under 1m, garden-bed step): $2,500-$4,500</li>
          <li>Full driveway + alfresco + side path package: $18,500-$28,500</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/officer/">Officer</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/beaconsfield/">Beaconsfield</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/pakenham/">Pakenham</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/heritage-springs/">Heritage Springs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-shire/">All Cardinia Shire</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Cardinia Lakes paving quote.</h2>
        <p>Low-maintenance materials honest cost comparison. Small-block design that keeps the kids&rsquo; play space.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
